This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a framework for few-shot learning that involves learning to learn a label-free loss function. The paper also uses neural networks as a key component of the proposed framework, which is a common technique in machine learning. Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on benchmark datasets commonly used in machine learning research, such as Mini-ImageNet and Caltech-UCSD Birds 200. 

The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it uses image datasets for evaluation and proposes a method for few-shot image classification. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely sub-category as the paper proposes a method for learning to learn, which is a key area of research in AI. 

Natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) are less likely sub-categories as the paper does not involve language processing or evolutionary algorithms.
